
URL = http://www.seriosity.com/

=Description=

"Seriosity is marketing a product called “Attent” that plugs into a user’s Microsoft Outlook. It uses '''a digital currency called “Serios,” which is attached to emails to signify urgency'''. When someone wants to get the attention of their boss, Attent crunches their boss’s “open rate” to indicate their boss needs at least 10 serios to even read the email. So the worker would then, say, attach 50 Serios for assurance the email would be read quickly.

Since each user only gets a finite number of Serios a week, the product creates a marketplace for attention. Users can “earn” Serios from each other by performing tasks, such as completing an assignment ahead of deadline, for instance.

Backers of this “new money” say it makes sense given the “gift economy” where information is abundant and more often, free. Whereas information may have been “scarce” before, the thinking goes, the market must adjust to these new scarcities, namely attention, trust, and reputation."
(http://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2009/09/09/the-currency-revolution/)


